Resource Groups should be designed based on application lifecycle and management requirements rather than individual resource types.

Recommended practices include:

* Group related resources together
* Separate Development, Test, and Production
* Apply RBAC consistently
* Use resource tags

For example, all resources supporting a production web application should belong to one production resource group.

A real-life use case is simplifying deployments, backups, and cleanup activities.

Well-designed resource groups improve administration and governance.
